        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integration Best Practices for API Teams"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To integrate BGE M3 efficiently, start by evaluating your application's throughput requirements. Use asynchronous calls for high-volume scenarios to reduce latency, and implement caching for repeated queries. Ensure error handling is robust to manage rate limits and avoid unnecessary API calls that inflate costs. Testing with mock data before deployment can help fine-tune performance without incurring charges."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance Optimization and Cost Management"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimize API usage by batching requests where possible, as this can lower per-request costs. Monitor metrics like response time and error rates using logging tools to identify inefficiencies. Regularly review your pricing tier against actual usage to adjust plans proactively. Additionally, consider implementing fallback mechanisms or hybrid approaches with local models to balance cost and performance during peak loads."
